Using the Popularity score column to create a new column- Popularity Binary. If the popularity score of the song is greater than 50, we are classifying the song as popular (assigning 1 to it). Otherwise, we are classying it as unpopular (assigning 0 to it)¶

In [15]:
df['Popularity_Binary'] = np.where(df['Popularity']>50, 1, 0)

Now we will run different models to try and predict whether the song is popular or not based on the clusters¶

SMOTE¶

Because our dataset is imbalanced(more popular songs than unpopular ones), we use the SMOTE method to resample to make our data balanced

In [21]:
Y= df.Popularity_Binary
X = df[['clust1', 'clust2', 'clust3']].values
In [23]:
#split the data into train and test sets
x_train, x_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, Y, test_size=0.2, random_state=10)

Logistic Regression¶

In [26]:
kf = StratifiedKFold(n_splits=10)

metrics_list = []
for fold, (train_index, test_index) in enumerate(kf.split(X, Y), 1):
    X_train = X[train_index]
    y_train = Y[train_index]  
    X_test = X[test_index]
    y_test = Y[test_index]  
    sm = SMOTE(sampling_strategy="minority", random_state=5)
    X_train_oversampled, y_train_oversampled = sm.fit_resample(X_train, y_train)
    model = LogisticRegression()
    model.fit(X_train_oversampled, y_train_oversampled ) 
    y_pred = model.predict(X_test)
    precision = precision_score(y_test, y_pred)
    recall = recall_score(y_test, y_pred)
    f1 = f1_score(y_test, y_pred)
    accuracy = accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred)

    
    print(f'For fold {fold}:')
    print(f'Accuracy: {model.score(X_test, y_test)}')
    print(f'f-score: {f1_score(y_test, y_pred)}')
    model_disp = plot_roc_curve(model, X_test, y_test)
    
    metrics_list.append({"accuracy": accuracy, "precision": precision, 
                         "recall": recall, "f1_score": f1})
    
    plt.show()    
    
    
metrics_df = pd.DataFrame(metrics_list)

    X_train = X[train_index]
    y_train = Y[train_index]  
    X_test = X[test_index]
    y_test = Y[test_index]  
    sm = SMOTE(sampling_strategy="minority", random_state=5)
    X_train_oversampled, y_train_oversampled = sm.fit_resample(X_train, y_train)
    model = DecisionTreeClassifier()

    precision = precision_score(y_test, y_pred)
    recall = recall_score(y_test, y_pred)
    f1 = f1_score(y_test, y_pred)
    accuracy = accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred)

kf = StratifiedKFold(n_splits=10)

metrics_list = []
for fold, (train_index, test_index) in enumerate(kf.split(X, Y), 1):
    X_train = X[train_index]
    y_train = Y[train_index]  
    X_test = X[test_index]
    y_test = Y[test_index]  
    sm = SMOTE(sampling_strategy="minority", random_state=5)
    X_train_oversampled, y_train_oversampled = sm.fit_resample(X_train, y_train)
    model = RandomForestClassifier()
    model.fit(X_train_oversampled, y_train_oversampled ) 
    y_pred = model.predict(X_test)
    precision = precision_score(y_test, y_pred)
    recall = recall_score(y_test, y_pred)
    f1 = f1_score(y_test, y_pred)
    accuracy = accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred)

    
    print(f'For fold {fold}:')
    print(f'Accuracy: {model.score(X_test, y_test)}')
    print(f'f-score: {f1_score(y_test, y_pred)}')
    model_disp = plot_roc_curve(model, X_test, y_test)
    
    metrics_list.append({"precision": precision, "recall": recall, 
                         "f1_score": f1, "accuracy": accuracy})
    
    plt.show()

KNN¶

In [34]:
kf = StratifiedKFold(n_splits=10)

metrics_list = []
for fold, (train_index, test_index) in enumerate(kf.split(X, Y), 1):
    X_train = X[train_index]
    y_train = Y[train_index]  
    X_test = X[test_index]
    y_test = Y[test_index]  
    sm = SMOTE(sampling_strategy="minority", random_state=5)
    X_train_oversampled, y_train_oversampled = sm.fit_resample(X_train, y_train)
    model = KNeighborsClassifier(n_neighbors = 10)
    model.fit(X_train_oversampled, y_train_oversampled ) 
    y_pred = model.predict(X_test)
    precision = precision_score(y_test, y_pred)
    recall = recall_score(y_test, y_pred)
    f1 = f1_score(y_test, y_pred)
    accuracy = accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred)

    
    print(f'For fold {fold}:')
    print(f'Accuracy: {model.score(X_test, y_test)}')
    print(f'f-score: {f1_score(y_test, y_pred)}')
    model_disp = plot_roc_curve(model, X_test, y_test)
    
    metrics_list.append({ "accuracy": accuracy, "precision": precision, 
                         "recall": recall, "f1_score": f1})
    
    plt.show()    
    
    
metrics_df = pd.DataFrame(metrics_list)

kf = StratifiedKFold(n_splits=10)

metrics_list = []
for fold, (train_index, test_index) in enumerate(kf.split(X, Y), 1):
    X_train = X[train_index]
    y_train = Y[train_index]  
    X_test = X[test_index]
    y_test = Y[test_index]  
    sm = SMOTE(sampling_strategy="minority", random_state=5)
    X_train_oversampled, y_train_oversampled = sm.fit_resample(X_train, y_train)
    model = svc
    model.fit(X_train_oversampled, y_train_oversampled ) 
    y_pred = model.predict(X_test)
    precision = precision_score(y_test, y_pred)
    recall = recall_score(y_test, y_pred)
    f1 = f1_score(y_test, y_pred)
    accuracy = accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred)

    
    print(f'For fold {fold}:')
    print(f'Accuracy: {model.score(X_test, y_test)}')
    print(f'f-score: {f1_score(y_test, y_pred)}')
    model_disp = plot_roc_curve(model, X_test, y_test)
    
    metrics_list.append({ "accuracy": accuracy, "precision": precision, 
                         "recall": recall, "f1_score": f1})
    
    plt.show()    
    
    
metrics_df = pd.DataFrame(metrics_list)

From the above table we see that KNeighborsClassifier performs the best. As a result we apply gridsearch to tune the parameters for this model.¶

In [42]:
%%time
from sklearn.model_selection import GridSearchCV
grid_params = {'n_neighbors': [3,5,7,9,11,13,15,1719], 
               'weights': ['uniform', 'distance'], 
               'metric': [ 'euclidean', 'manhattan']}

gs= GridSearchCV(
    KNeighborsClassifier (),
    grid_params,
    verbose = 1,
    cv = 3,
    n_jobs = -1 )
gs_results = gs.fit (X_train, y_train)

In [44]:
kf = StratifiedKFold(n_splits=10)

metrics_list = []
for fold, (train_index, test_index) in enumerate(kf.split(X, Y), 1):
    X_train = X[train_index]
    y_train = Y[train_index]  
    X_test = X[test_index]
    y_test = Y[test_index]  
    sm = SMOTE(sampling_strategy="minority", random_state=5)
    X_train_oversampled, y_train_oversampled = sm.fit_resample(X_train, y_train)
    model = KNeighborsClassifier(n_neighbors = 9, weights= 'uniform', metric='euclidean')
    model.fit(X_train_oversampled, y_train_oversampled ) 
    y_pred = model.predict(X_test)
    precision = precision_score(y_test, y_pred)
    recall = recall_score(y_test, y_pred)
    f1 = f1_score(y_test, y_pred)
    accuracy = accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred)

    
    print(f'For fold {fold}:')
    print(f'Accuracy: {model.score(X_test, y_test)}')
    print(f'f-score: {f1_score(y_test, y_pred)}')
    model_disp = plot_roc_curve(model, X_test, y_test)
    
    metrics_list.append({ "accuracy": accuracy, "precision": precision, 
                         "recall": recall, "f1_score": f1})
    
    plt.show()    
    
    
metrics_df = pd.DataFrame(metrics_list)
